# title = The Dog and the Snail
# sent_id = perry-253-s1
# text = Ὤα τις κύων καταπίνειν εἰθισμένος, ἰδών τινα κόχλον, χάνας τὸ στόμα αὐτοῦ, μεγίστῃ συνολκῇ καταπέπωκε τοῦτον, οἰηθεὶς ὠὸν εἶναι.
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p253/s1
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = A certain dog accustomed to swallowing eggs, seeing a snail, gaping its mouth, has swallowed it with the greatest pull, thinking it was an egg.
# literal_translation = Eggs a certain dog to swallow accustomed, having seen a certain snail, having gaped its mouth, with the greatest pull has swallowed it, having thought an egg to be.
